bib.title: Inelastic scattering of 100 MeV protons from Mg andSi using a Ge(Li) total absorption proton counter

free_txt: by observing the spectrum of protons scattered from
12C. This nucleus yields a proton spectrum having
well-spaced peaks of well-known energies. Plastic E
counter preceded by a standard counter telescope and
scattering chamber. The overall resolution of the
plastic counter telescope for 100 MeV protons was 1.3
MeV and consequently in both 24Mg and 28Si the
elastic and first-excited states were not resolved.
A cooled Ge(Li) detector was used as the total
absorption proton counter for the energy analysis of
100 MeV protons scattered from targets. The inelastic
peak areas were converted to absolute cross sections
by a separate measurement of the absolute
differential elastic scattering cross sections using
a multi-purpose laboratory scattering facility. The
Ge(Li) detector was calibrated by observing the
estimates of the ranges of protons in germanium.
